cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a model for album storytelling that involves encoding photos and scenes hierarchically to generate a coherent story. The model uses semantic representations and temporal relationships among photos, which suggests that it may fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of a reconstructor to extract semantic information from the album and the end-to-end training approach suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
